<h3 class="title-sect">Guide to Personal Information Collection and Use</h3>
<div class="terms-box" tabindex="0">
	<div class="terms-inner">
		<strong>1. Personal Information Handling Guidelines</strong>
		<p>01. General Provisions</p>
		<p>
			“Personal information” refers to the personally identifiable information such as name, resident registration number, and videos (including videos that cannot be used to identify a person by themselves but can easily be combined with other information to identify that person). “Data subject” refers to the person who may be identified by the handled data and serves as the agent of the same data. The
			company ensures that the Personal Information Handling Guidelines remains easily identifiable any time by disclosing them on the main page of its website (http:///www.dohwa.co.kr). If it revises the Personal Information Handling Guidelines, the company will announce it through Notices on its website (or through announcements to individual users).
		</p>
		<p>02. Personal Information Items Processed and Their Purpose</p>
		<p>The company does not process sensitive information that may seriously infringe on privacy or personally identifiable data that can identify an individual in accordance with the relevant law or regulation or without the consent of the data subject.</p>
		<p>
			A. Items Processed
			<br />
			Name (Korean/Sino-Korean/English), photo, password, home phone number, home address, permanent domicile, mobile phone number, email address, education, military service (completed or not, service period, service category, rank), language skills, computer skills, qualifications, family relations, eligibility for veteran’s benefits, work experience, social relations, honors, overseas experience,
			research experience
		</p>
		<p>
			B. Purpose of Data Processing
			<br />
			- For recruiting procedures or to communicate with applicants
			<br />
			- Human resources management including payment of salary, provision of welfare benefits, training, subscription to credit guarantee insurance, support for implementation and evaluation of various tasks
		</p>
		<p>03. Personal Information Processing and Retention Period</p>
		<p>By principle, when the purpose of the collection and use of the personal information is fulfilled, the specific data shall be destroyed immediately. However, the data below shall be retained for respectively specified periods, and when necessary, the consent of the data subject shall be obtained.</p>
		<p>
			A. Personal information of a Hired Job Applicant
			<br />
			- Retention period: Permanently
			<br />
			- Reason for retention: Human resources management during the person’s employment, welfare benefits after retirement, issuance of employment certificate, etc.
			<br />
			- Items retained: Name (Korean/Sino-Korean/English), photo, password, home phone number, home address, permanent domicile, mobile phone number, email address, education, military service
			<br />
			(completed or not, service period, service category, rank), language skills, computer skills, qualifications, family relations, eligibility for veteran’s benefits, work experience, social relations, honors, overseas experience, research experience
		</p>
		<p>
			B. Personal Information of a Job Applicant Who Is not Hired
			<br />
			- Retention period: 5 years from the completion of the recruiting procedure
			<br />
			- Reasons for retention: For management of human resources that may be hired in the future
			<br />
			- Name (Korean/Sino-Korean/English), photo, password, home phone number, home address, permanent domicile, mobile phone number, email address, education, military service (completed or not, service period, service category, rank), language skills, computer skills, qualifications, family relations, eligibility for veteran’s benefits, work experience, social relations, honors, overseas experience,
			research experience
		</p>
		<p>04. How Personal Information is Destroyed</p>
		<p>
			Personal information saved in the form of an electronic file shall be destroyed using a technical method that disables the playback of the record.
			<br />
			Personal information printed on paper shall be pulverized with a pulverizer or destroyed through incineration.
		</p>
		<br />
		<p>
			Disclosed date: Jan. 1, 2012
			<br />
			Enforced date: Jan. 1, 2012
		</p>
	</div>
</div>
